one parish in Devon. It is merely another spelling of Richard."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":29,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":38,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":49,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":65,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":67,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Rycharde Puttyepoole was born in 1520, in Great Warley, Essex, England as the son of John Puttypole and Amy Person. He married Joane Boxer on 4 May 1561, in South Weald, Essex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 19 November 1587, in Barking, Essex, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1520–19 November 1587":"1520–19. november 1587","1520–1587":"1520–1587","1525–1593":"1525–1593","1577–1645":"1577–1645","1485–1551":"1485–1551","–1557":"–1557","1593":"1593","March 25 1557":"märts 1557","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1525":"1525","1557":"1557","1645":"1645","1577":"1577","1587":"1587","1520":"1520","04 MAY 1561":"4. mai 1561","1585":"1585","1551":"1551","1485":"1485","25 Mar 1551":"25. märts 1551","26 May 1577":"26. mai 1577","19 November 1587":"19. november 1587","1549":"1549","Great Warley, Essex, England":"Great Warley, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barking, Essex, England":"Barking, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barking, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Barking, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","South Weald, Essex, England":"South Weald, Essex, England"},"fi":{"1520–19 November 1587":"1520–19. marraskuuta 1587","1520–1587":"1520–1587","1525–1593":"1525–1593","1577–1645":"1577–1645","1485–1551":"1485–1551","–1557":"–1557","1593":"1593","March 25 1557":"maaliskuu 1557","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1525":"1525","1557":"1557","1645":"1645","1577":"1577","1587":"1587","1520":"1520","04 MAY 1561":"4. toukokuuta 1561","1585":"1585","1551":"1551","1485":"1485","25 Mar 1551":"25. maaliskuuta 1551","26 May 1577":"26. toukokuuta 1577","19 November 1587":"19. marraskuuta 1587","1549":"1549","Great Warley, Essex, England":"Great Warley, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Barking, Essex, England":"Barking, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Barking, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Barking, Es